.SH NAME
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
break \- Sets or clears extended CTRL+C checking.
.
.
.
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH SYNOPSIS
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.
.SY break
.OP /?
.RI [ state ]
.YS
.
.
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH DESCRIPTION
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.
Sets or Clears Extended CTRL+C checking on DOS system.
.
This is present for Compatibility with DOS systems. It has no effect
under Windows.
.
If Command Extensions are enabled, and running on the Windows
platform, then the
.B break
command will enter a hard coded breakpoint if being debugged by a debugger.
.
.
.
.
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH OPTIONS
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.
.TP
.B /?
Display help and exit. Other options are ignored.
.
.TP
.I state
.
.RS
.
.TP
.B on
.
Turns on the break, which allows the Ctrl+C function.
.
.TP
.B off
.
Turns off the break, not allowing Ctrl+C to cancel a process.
.
.RE
.
.TP
any other parameter
.
All other values of parameter are silently ignored.
.
.
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.
.TP
.B 0
.
Command
.B break
always returns exit code 0.
.
.
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.
.TP
.B ERRORLEVEL
.
Command
.B break
set environment variable %ERRORLEVEL% to command exit status.
.
.
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH REGISTRY
.\" --------------------------------------------------------------------
.
.
.
